The President of the United States issued a statement condemning the murder of Japanese journalist Kenji Goto by the terrorist group ISIL. Goto had been reporting on the plight of the Syrian people. The President expressed condolences to Goto's family and stood in solidarity with Prime Minister Abe and the Japanese people in denouncing the act. The statement also praised Japan's commitment to peace and prosperity in the Middle East and globally, including its assistance to those affected by conflicts in the region. The United States, along with its allies and partners, will continue to take action to degrade and destroy ISIL.